+// waitForEvents is called by the scheduler when the runqueue is
+// empty and no sleeping/timer tasks are pending. In userspace (Ring 3)
+// we cannot execute sti/cli/hlt, so the best we can do is a no-op
+// fallback — if the runqueue truly has no future wake source this is
+// a deadlock, but the kernel will still preempt us on timer IRQ.
